    <stitle>2 SPEED AND DOUBLE REDUCTION SINGLE DRIVE AXLES: EATON - REMOVE</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>REMOVE</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="1">
            <title>DIFFERENTIAL CARRIER ASSEMBLY</title>
            <para>Follow procedure in numerical sequence. Step numbers correspond to numbers in
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1401604">Figure 4</hotlnk>.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1401604" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1401604" filename="../figg14/G1401604.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 4. Differential Carrier Assembly</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">
                    <emph type="bold">2-Speed Axle Only</emph>
                    - Shift Axle to Low Range.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Drain lubricant.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Disconnect drive shaft.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove axle shafts, stud nuts, lockwashers and taper dowels (if used). If necessary,
                    loosen dowels by holding a brass drift in the center of the shaft head and striking it a sharp blow
                    with a hammer.
                </para>
                <specpara>
                    <warning>
                        <para>Wear safe eye protection. Do not hit steel parts with a steel hammer. Parts can break and
                            cause injury.
                        </para>
                    </warning>
                </specpara>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">
                    <emph type="bold">2-Speed Axle Only</emph>
                    - Disconnect shift unit air lines or electrical wires. Remove shift units.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>When shift unit or axle shaft is removed, provide container to catch oil that escapes from
                        reservoir.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove nuts, bolts and washers fastening carrier to axle housing. Remove differential
                    carrier assembly.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>To prevent personal injury, do not lie under carrier while removing fasteners or after
                        fasteners are removed. Use transmission jack to support and remove differential carrier
                        assembly.
                    </para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>If replacing carrier assembly as a unit, refer to
                        <hotlnk document="s14016_HL1401614.xml" xrefid="hl1401614">INSTALL, DIFFERENTIAL CARRIER
                            ASSEMBLY</hotlnk>, for instructions.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
